rComments: Interesting readings, inspirational lectures, intelligent, and always kind and approachable to students.

This class was disappointing. The prof lectures by reading directly off of lecture slides, which she doesn't post online. The level of difficulty of marking did not reflect the quality of instruction, way to harsh of a marker. However, there are 3 quizzes throughout the semester and if you show up to class its not hard to get perfect.

Just everything you want in a professor: intelligent, caring while really opening your mind on the issues in Canadian history. 1000000% would take another course with her! Best professor Ive had in the department as a history major.

Overall Prof Bertram is a great professor. She's INCREDIBLY knowledgeable in her field and is always willing to help you when you have questions or need help with the assignments. There is a bit of reading but it's all really interesting, the class is almost over and not one dry reading yet. Great course! HIGHLY recommend, opens a totally new world
